elements.title: Saint Juliana Olshanskaya
elements.contents: ... that Saint Juliana Olshanskaya (pictured) is said to have appeared to Archimandrite Peter Mogila to reproach him for the lack of respect paid to her relics?

elements.title: a 1994 lightning strike
elements.contents: ... that a 1994 lightning strike in Egypt led to 469 deaths after oil tanks were ignited and flooded the village of Dronka with burning fuel?

elements.title: first Division I college sports championship
elements.contents: ... that the first Division I college sports championship won by a historically black university in any sport was vacated by the NCAA?

elements.title: Karma Man
elements.contents: ... that the Buddhist themes of David Bowie's 1967 composition "Karma Man" were compared to the Marvel Comics character Doctor Strange?

elements.title: Francis B. Murdoch
elements.contents: ... that lawyer Francis B. Murdoch filed one-third of all freedom suits in St. Louis from 1840 to 1847, representing Dred Scott, Harriet Robinson Scott, Lucy A. Delaney and Polly Berry, among others?

elements.title: Ontario Highway 78
elements.contents: ... that the North Branch Bridge on Ontario Highway 78 partially collapsed just 17 days after a temporary bridge was opened to facilitate construction of a replacement?

elements.title: Barrau de Sescas
elements.contents: ... that Barrau de Sescas, a Gascon knight, was the first person appointed by an English king to a position titled admiral?

elements.title: Catalena Productions
elements.contents: ... that Catalena Productions had a Monty Hall problem when the host, unpaid, forced the company into bankruptcy?
